title.narrative: China-Second Liaoning Medium Cities Infrastructure Project

description.narrative: The project development objective is to improve the performance and sustainability of water supply, wastewater, and solid waste services in the LMC-2 cities. Enhanced wastewater and solid waste services will also help reduce pollution into the Bohai Sea and contribute to improving Bohai Sea water quality.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :LA, Schedule 2, Section 2, para. A1 | Description :LUCRPO to produce semi-annual progress reports | Frequency:Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Schedule, Section I, para. 11 | Description :Project Companies, Fushun and Gaizhou to implement financialimprovement plans | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Schedule, Section I, para. 5b | Description :Gaizhou to complete dam safety remedial work | Due Date:31-May-2009

Finance Agreement :PA, Schedule, Section I, para. 6 | Description :Fushun, Panjin and Yingkou EDZ to prepare and subsequentlyimplement comprehensive solid waste strategic plan acceptable to the Bank | Due Date :01-Dec-2014
Finance Agreement :PA, Schedule, Section I, para. 8 | Description :Fushun to transfer all drainage assets to Drainage Company | DueDate :01-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :PA, Schedule, Section I, para. 9 | Description :Prepare no later than December 1, 2014, annual water andwastewater utility performance report for cities participating in the project. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Schedule, Section I, para.5c | Description :LUCRPO to update Dahoufang dam's O&M and emergency preparednessplan satisfactory to the Bank | Due Date :31-May-2009
Finance Agreement :PA, Schedule, Section I, paras. 2-3 | Description :Project Cities to implement RAPs and EMPs satisfactory to theBank | Frequency :Yearly
